TY  - JOUR
T1  - Enhancing a Branch-and-Bound Algorithm for Two-Stage Stochastic Integer Network Design-Based Models
AU  - Andrade, Rafael
AU  - Lisser, Abdel
AU  - Maculan, Nelson
AU  - Plateau, Gérard
Y1  - 2006/09/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1060.0536
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.1060.0536
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1450
EP  - 1455
VL  - 52
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In this paper we present branch-and-bound (B&B) strategies for two-stage stochastic integer network design-based models with integrality constraints in the first-stage variables. These strategies are used within L-shaped decomposition-based B&B framework. We propose a valid inequality in order to improve B&B performance. We use this inequality to implement a multirooted B&B tree. A selective use of optimality cuts is explored in the B&B approach and we also propose a subgradient-based technique for branching on 0-1 feasible solutions. Finally, we present computational results for a fixed-charge network design problem with random demands.
AB  - In this paper we present branch-and-bound (B&B) strategies for two-stage stochastic integer network design-based models with integrality constraints in the first-stage variables. These strategies are used within L-shaped decomposition-based B&B framework. We propose a valid inequality in order to improve B&B performance. We use this inequality to implement a multirooted B&B tree. A selective use of optimality cuts is explored in the B&B approach and we also propose a subgradient-based technique for branching on 0-1 feasible solutions. Finally, we present computational results for a fixed-charge network design problem with random demands.
